# File Organization & Naming

- Command handlers: `src/features/{feature}/application/handlers/command-handlers/{action}-{entity}.handler.ts`
- Query handlers: `src/features/{feature}/application/handlers/query-handlers/{action}-{entity}.handler.ts`
- Commands: `src/features/{feature}/application/contracts/commands/{action}-{entity}.command.ts`
- Queries: `src/features/{feature}/application/contracts/queries/{action}-{entity}.query.ts`
- DTOs: `src/features/{feature}/application/contracts/dtos/{entity}.dto.ts`
- Entities: `src/features/{feature}/infrastructure/entities/{entity}.entity.ts`
- Services: `src/features/{feature}/domain/services/{entity}.service.ts`
- Controllers: `src/features/{feature}/client/controllers/{entity}s.controller.ts`
- Events: `src/features/{feature}/domain/events/{entity}-{action}.event.ts`
- Use kebab-case for file names and directories.
- Use PascalCase for class names and interfaces.
- Use camelCase for method and property names.
- Group related functionality within feature directories.
